<item>
            <title>[THRIFT-156] Patch to Ruby HTTPClient to support SSL and to send correct Thrift Content-Type header</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/THRIFT-156</link>
                <project id="12310800" key="THRIFT">Thrift</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The Ruby HTTPClient class fails if you provide an https: URL, and it does not set the same HTTP Content-Type header as the other language libraries.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This small patch addresses these two issues:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Index: lib/rb/lib/thrift/transport/httpclient.rb&lt;br/&gt;
===================================================================&lt;br/&gt;
&amp;#8212; lib/rb/lib/thrift/transport/httpclient.rb	(revision 701711)&lt;br/&gt;
+++ lib/rb/lib/thrift/transport/httpclient.rb	(working copy)&lt;br/&gt;
@@ -1,6 +1,7 @@&lt;br/&gt;
 require &apos;thrift/transport&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; require &apos;net/http&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
+require &apos;net/https&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
 require &apos;uri&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
 require &apos;stringio&apos;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@@ -17,7 +18,9 @@&lt;br/&gt;
     def write(buf); @outbuf &amp;lt;&amp;lt; buf end&lt;br/&gt;
     def flush&lt;br/&gt;
       http = Net::HTTP.new @url.host, @url.port&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;alternate&quot; type=&quot;square&quot;&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;resp, data = http.post(@url.path, @outbuf)&lt;br/&gt;
+      http.use_ssl = @url.scheme == &quot;https&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
+      headers = 
{ &apos;Content-Type&apos; =&amp;gt; &apos;application/x-thrift&apos; }
&lt;p&gt;+      resp, data = http.post(@url.path, @outbuf, headers)&lt;br/&gt;
       @inbuf = StringIO.new data&lt;br/&gt;
       @outbuf = &quot;&quot;&lt;br/&gt;
     end&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
</description>
